{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-09T08:25:58.052531477Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-df6316d5","body":"Wire planned-elsewhere findings through the actual final-review/reconciliation path instead of only adding a standalone helper. `src/contexts/workflow_composition/panel_contracts.rs:137-154` still only allows free-form amendments, `src/contexts/workflow_composition/final_review.rs:1523-1553` still marks any accepted amendment as `restart_required`, and `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:7359-7378` still turns every accepted final-review item into a `QueuedAmendment`. The new handler in `src/contexts/automation_runtime/planned_elsewhere.rs:81-158` is not invoked from that flow, so there is currently no way to carry `mapped_to_bead_id` through review or let the active bead complete without a reopen/restart loop.","dedup_key":"abce149ad06611fc5f7a15081b4cb0d3b6228f4a94ab3db28dcbb59ef50757de","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260409075617","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-09T08:25:58.061894162Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-170d2fcc","body":"Make `record_planned_elsewhere_mapping` transactional across `planned_elsewhere.ndjson` and the milestone journal. In `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2352-2380` the mapping file is appended first and the `PlannedElsewhereMapped` journal event is appended second, with no rollback if `append_event` fails. A journal write error will therefore leave a persisted mapping with no audit event.","dedup_key":"f3ec8aa0e796b035fc497474994492aea6d0acd9e8556cda637b422efeb74271","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260409075617","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":19,"timestamp":"2026-04-09T08:25:58.071332821Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-4eed62c2","body":"Tighten stale-bead fallback so only definitive missing/closed bead results are downgraded to warnings. In `src/contexts/automation_runtime/planned_elsewhere.rs:55-73`, any `br show` failure is treated as `bead_verified = false` and reconciliation proceeds. Timeouts, parse failures, or repo/configuration errors would therefore be misclassified as stale-bead cases instead of surfacing an operator-visible failure.","dedup_key":"817fc369965b6aae59528f38b6ede135d08b10f49c27c79d1ba40267091b3f62","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260409075617","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
